FAQs






            Benefits
          Heading link



 
Copy link






                            How can I get care during the pandemic?
                    








            COVID 19
          

Contact your CampusCare primary care provider for directions of care. See our COVID 19 website for information regarding temporary policies.







                            What are my member rights & responsibilities?
                    








            Rights & Responsibilities
          

Member rights and responsibilities can be found here.







                            What are my CampusCare benefits?
                    








            Benefits
          

CampusCare is a self-funded student health benefit plan that works like a traditional HMO plan. CampusCare works in conjunction with the Student Health Service Fee to provide student at UIC comprehensive health benefits. Information regarding the benefits provided by CampusCare can be found here.







                            Does CampusCare cover vision & dental benefits?
                    








            Dental Benefits
          

CampusCare members are enrolled in discount vision & dental programs run through a third party company, United Health Programs. This program offers a discount at vision & dental providers that in-network with United Health Programs. More information regarding this can be found here for vision and  here for dental. 







                            When does coverage begin?
                    








            Coverage dates
          

CampusCare is a semester based program. Click here for information regarding coverage dates.







                            How do I get my CampusCare ID?
                    








            CampusCare ID Card
          

Students can use their i-Card at UI Health. Members can also download and print their CampusCare ID card from the CampusCare portal. Instructions for downloading and printing your CampusCare ID card can be found here.







                            How do I make a doctor's appointment?
                    








            Primary Care
          

Members should call their CampusCare Primary Care Provider’s office to schedule non-emergency care.







                            Is CampusCare Primary or Secondary?
                    








            CampusCare as secondary insurance
          

CampusCare is secondary to all other insurance companies except Medicaid. More information can be found here.







                            I lost my health insurance, how can I get CampusCare Coverage?
                    








            Reinstatement
          

We allow currently registered students to reinstate into CampusCare at any time by submitting an electronic reinstatement request via our portal. If a student reinstates after the established deadline date, their effective date of coverage is the date the reinstatement form is submitted. More information on reinstating into CampusCare can be found here.







                            Which dependents can I add to CampusCare?
                    








            Dependents
          

Members can add spouses, civil union partners and eligible children to their CampusCare coverage for an additional fee. More information regarding add dependents can be found here.







                            How do I add dependents to CampusCare?
                    








            Adding Dependents
          

During the open enrollment period, or after a qualifying life event, students can submit a dependent add request via the CampusCare portal and upload the required documentation prior to the open enrollment period deadline date. Dependents are automatically carried over each semester that a member is registered for courses unless a drop dependent request is submitted via the CampusCare portal prior to the deadline date for the semester. More information regarding adding dependents can be found here.







                            Am I eligible for CampusCare?
                    








            Eligiblity
          

Eligible students include all registered Undergraduate, Graduate, and Health Professional students taking at least one class that charges them with tuition and mandatory fees. Eligible fellows working under a T/32, F/32, T/42, T/76, or D43 grant at UIC are also eligible for CampusCare (to verify if you are eligible please contact your program administrator). To verify if you are a member, students can view the CampusCare charge by going to their student account bill (E-Bill). If you are not charged with the CampusCare Fee you are not a member of CampusCare. Information regarding eligibility can be found here.







                            How do I waive CampusCare if I have my own insurance?
                    








            Waiving CampusCare
          

Students can submit a waiver via our website prior to the deadline date for the semester. Waivers are good for one academic year: Fall, Spring & Summer, in that order. All waivers must be resubmitted each academic year. Click here for information regarding waiving CampusCare.







                            How much does CampusCare cost?
                    








            cost
          

CampusCare is a semester based program. Information regarding cost can be found here.







                            I am not taking classes for Summer, am I still covered by CampusCare?
                    








            Summer Coverage
          

Students that are NOT taking summer classes or are graduating, and have CampusCare coverage for the Spring term of that academic year, are able to continue CampusCare coverage through the Summer by completing and submitting a Summer Continuation Form by the Enrollment Period Deadline Date.







                            Where do I send my pharmacy/medical claims?
                    








            Claims
          

Our claims address is:
CampusCare
PO Box 8030
Westchester, IL 60154
Information regarding claims can be found here.







                            I received a bill for a medical service that should be covered under CampusCare, who do I contact?
                    








            Claims
          

Please contact our claims department at 312-996-4915 option 2.
 







                            How do I change my mailing address in the University system for CampusCare?
                    








            UIC Information
          

You information with CampusCare will automatically change when you update your information in the UIC system.




















 
